	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">meaning any RAM primarily used by a video chip.</div><br />Which also includes name and attribute tables, OAM and palette memory.</div>
<br />True. But in practice, OAM and the palette are part of the PPU chip, not discrete components visible on the external bus, and not part of what is normally called "VRAM".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
